<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id90f91e06-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s8302"><num value="8302">§ 8302.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id90f91e07-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s8302/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> VfP Office</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “VfP Office” means the Office of Volunteers for Prosperity of the United States Agency for International Development.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id90f91e08-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s8302/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> VfP Program</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “VfP Program” means the Volunteers for Prosperity Program established through Executive Order 13317.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id90f91e09-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s8302/3"><num value="3" class="bold">(3)</num><heading class="bold"> VfPServe</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “VfPServe” means a program established by the VfP Office, in cooperation with the USA Freedom Corps, to provide eligible skilled professionals with fixed amount stipends to offset the travel and living costs of volunteering abroad.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id90f91e0a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/13/tV/s5102">Pub. L. 111–13, title V, § 5102</ref>, <date date="2009-04-21">Apr. 21, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/1598">123 Stat. 1598</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id90f91e0b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id90f91e0c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id90f91e0d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Executive Order 13317, referred to in par. (2), is set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s8301">section 8301 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id90f91e0e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id90f91e0f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="2009-10-01">Oct. 1, 2009</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/111/13/s6101/a">section 6101(a) of Pub. L. 111–13</ref>, set out as an Effective Date of 2009 Amendment note under <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s4950">section 4950 of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare.</p>
</note>
</notes>
